miral (Australia)|Vice Admiral]] [[Michael Noonan (admiral)|Michael Noonan]]) (6 July 2018)\n##[[Chief of Army (Australia)|Chief of Army]] ([[Lieutenant general (Australia)|Lieutenant General]] [[Rick Burr|Richard Burr]]) (2 July 2018)\n##[[Chief of Air Force (Australia)|Chief of Air Force]] ([[Air marshal (Australia)|Air Marshal]] [[Mel Hupfeld]]) (July 2019)\n#Consuls-General, Consuls and Vice-Consuls according to the date on which recognition was granted\n#[[Members of the Australian Capital Territory Legislative Assembly, 2016\u20132020|Members of the Australian Capital Territory Legislative Assembly]]\n#[[Australian honours system|Recipients of Decorations or Honours from the Sovereign]]\n#Citizens of the Commonwealth of Australia\n\n==Notes==\n\n* The Location of Officials matters for precedence; an official enjoys different precedence within and without his or her state.\n* Each State and Territory also has its own Table of Precedence.\n* The recipients of Decorations or Honours gain precedence in the order of Seniority or Superiority of the Orders themselves; the Orders of Knighthood in Australia have the same seniority as in the United Kingdom, with a few insertions or promotions of entirely Australian, non-British honours; see [[Australian Honours Order of Wearing]].\n* No reference is made to the [[Chief Minister of the Australian Capital Territory|Chief Minister]], the [[Leader of the Opposition (Australian Capital Territory)|Leader of the Opposition]] or the [[Speaker of the Australian Capital Territory Legislative Assembly|Speaker]] of the [[Australian Capital Territory]]. This appears to be an oversight after the ACT was granted [[Australian Capital Territory (Self-Government) Act 1988|self government]]. This had been raised with the Chief Minister and the Leader of the Opposition and was expected to be resolved in 2015.<ref>{{cite news|first=Tom|last=McIlroy|title=Canberra's diplomatic mistake \u2013 25 years in the making|url=http://www.canberratimes.com.au/act-news/canberras-diplomatic-mistake--25-years-in-the-making-20150226-12uo3v.html|newspaper=[[The Canberra Times]]|date=26 February 2015|accessdate=8 July 2015}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n*[http://picpaste.com/pics/precedence.1221713538.jpg Table of Precedence for the Commonwealth of Australia]\u2013 as Gazetted in Special Gazette No. S206 on Tuesday, 5 October 1982. Note, this pre dates ACT Self Government, 1988.\n*[http://dfat.gov.au/about-us/publications/corporate/protocol-guidelines/Pages/appendix-22-commonwealth-table-of-precedence.aspx Protocol Guidelines, Appendix 22, Commonwealth Table of Precedence]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Table Of Precedence For The Commonwealth Of Australia}}\n[[Category:Orders of precedence|Australia]]\n[[Category:Australia politics-related lists|Order of precedence, Australian]]\n[[Category:Government of Australia|Order of precedence]]\n", "name_user": "JackofOz", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Table_of_precedence_for_the_Commonwealth_of_Australia"}
