end}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[2013 Davis Cup]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.fedcup.com/ 2013 Fed Cup]\n\n{{Fed Cup}}\n{{2013 in tennis}}\n{{2013 WTA Tour}}\n\n[[Category:2013 Fed Cup| ]]\n[[Category:2013 in tennis|Fed Cup]]\n[[Category:Fed Cups by year]]\n[[Category:2013 in women's tennis]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox tennis circuit season\n| name          = 2013 Fed Cup\n<!-- Commented out: | image =  -->\n| image_caption = \n| image_alt     = \n| image_size    = 250px\n| duration      = 9 February\u2013 3 November\n| edition       = 51st\n| tournaments   = \n| categories    = \n| previous      = [[2012 Fed Cup|2012]]\n| next          = [[2014 Fed Cup|2014]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2013 [[Fed Cup]]''' (also known as the '''2013 Fed Cup by [[BNP Paribas]]''' for sponsorship purposes) was the 51st edition of the most important tournament between national teams in women's [[tennis]].\n\nThe draw took place on 6 June 2012 in [[Paris]], France.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.fedcup.com/en/news/articles/draw-made-for-2013-fed-cup.aspx|title=Draw made for 2013 Fed Cup|accessdate=14 July 2012|publisher=fedcup.com}}</ref>\n\nThe final took place at the [[Tennis Club Cagliari]] in [[Cagliari]], [[Italy]], on 1\u20132 November. The home and three time champions [[Italy Fed Cup team|Italy]] defeated the fourth-seeded [[Russia Fed Cup team|Russia]], to win their fourth title.<ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2013/nov/03/italy-sara-errani-fed-cup|title= Sara Errani secures Fed Cup for Italy with win over Alisa Kleybanova|date=3 November 2013|work= Guardian |accessdate=4 November 2013}}</ref>\n{{TOC limit|3}}\n== World Group ==\n{{details|2013 Fed Cup World Group}}\n===Participating teams===\n{{colbegin|colwidth=18em}}\n* {{fed|AUS}}\n* {{fed|CZE}}\n* {{fed|ITA}}\n* {{fed|JPN}}\n* {{fed|RUS}}\n* {{fed|SRB}}\n* {{fed|SVK}}\n* {{fed|USA}}\n{{colend}}\n\n=== Draw ===\n{{8TeamBracket-info\n| RD1-date=9\u201310 February\n| RD2-date=20\u201321 April\n| RD3-date=2\u20133 November\n| teamwidth=16\n| RD1T1-loc={{nowrap|[[Ostrava]], [[Czech Republic]] (Indoor hard)}}\n| RD1-seed1=1 | RD1-team1= {{nowrap|{{fed|CZE}}}} | RD1-score1=4\n| RD1-seed2= | RD1-team2= {{fed|AUS}} | RD1-score2=0\n\n| RD1T2-loc= [[Rimini]], [[Italy]] (Indoor clay)\n| RD1-seed3= | RD1-team3= {{fed|USA}} | RD1-score3=2\n| RD1-seed4=3 | RD1-team4= {{fed|ITA}} | RD1-score4=3\n\n| RD1T3-loc= [[Moscow]], [[Russia]] (Indoor hard)\n| RD1-seed5=4 | RD1-team5= {{fed|RUS}} | RD1-score5=3\n| RD1-seed6= | RD1-team6= {{fed|JPN}} | RD1-score6=2\n\n| RD1T4-loc= [[Ni\u0161]], [[Serbia]] (Indoor hard)\n| RD1-seed7= | RD1-team7= {{fed|SVK}} | RD1-score7=3\n| RD1-seed8=2 | RD1-team8= {{fed|SRB}} | RD1-score8=2\n\n| RD2T1-loc= [[Palermo]], [[Italy]] (Outdoor clay)\n| RD2-seed1=1 | RD2-team1={{nowrap|{{fed|CZE}}}} | RD2-score1=1\n| RD2-seed2=3 | RD2-team2={{fed|ITA}} | RD2-score2=3\n\n| RD2T2-loc=[[Moscow]], [[Russia]] (Indoor clay)\n| RD2-seed3=4 | RD2-team3={{fed|RUS}} | RD2-score3=3\n| RD2-seed4= | RD2-team4={{fed|SVK}} | RD2-score4=2\n\n| RD3T1-loc=[[Cagliari]], [[Italy]] (Outdoor clay)\n| RD3-seed1=3 | RD3-team1={{fed|ITA}} | RD3-score1=4\n| RD3-seed2=4 | RD3-team2={{fed|RUS}} | RD3-score2=0\n\n}}\n\n==World Group II==\n{{details|2013 Fed Cup World Group II}}\nThe '''World Group II''' was the second highest level of Fed Cup competition in 2013. Winners advanced to the World Group Play-offs, and the losers played in the World Group II Play-offs.\n\nDate: 9\u201310 February\n{| class=wikitable cellspacing=\"1\" cellpadding=\"3\" style=\"border:1px solid #AAAAAA;\"\n|-\n!Venue!!Surface!!Home Team!!Score!!Visiting Team\n|-\n| Sporthalle Wankdorf, [[Bern]], [[Switzerland]]\n| Indoor hard\n|'''{{fed|SUI}}\n|align=center|4\u20131\n|{{fed|BEL}} <small>(1)</small>\n|-\n| [[Estadio Mary Ter\u00e1n de Weiss]], [[Buenos Aires]], [[Argentina]]\n| Outdoor clay\n|{{fed|ARG}} \n|align=center|2\u20133\n|'''{{fed|SWE}}''' <small>(4)</small>\n|-\n| Club Atl\u00e9tico Montemar, [[Alicante]], [[Spain]]\n| Outdoor clay\n|'''{{fed|ESP}} \n|align=center|3\u20131\n|{{fed|UKR}} <small>(3)</small>\n|-\n| [[Palais des Sports de Beaublanc]], [[Limoges]], [[France]]\n| Indoor clay\n|{{fed|FRA}}\n|align=center|1\u20133\n|'''{{fed|GER}}''' <small>(2)</small>\n|}\n\n== World Group Play-offs ==\n{{details|2013 Fed Cup World Group Play-offs}}\nThe four losing teams in the World Group first round ties, and four winners of the World Group II ties entered the draw for the World Group Play-offs. Four seeded teams, based on the latest Fed Cup ranking, were drawn against four unseeded teams.\n\nDate: 20\u201321 April\n{| class=wikitable cellspacing=\"1\" cellpadding=\"3\" style=\"border:1px solid #AAAAAA;\"\n|-\n!Venue!!Surface!!Home Team!!Score!!Visiting Team\n|-\n| [[Porsche Arena]], [[Stuttgart]], [[Germany]]\n| Indoor clay\n| '''{{fed|DEU}}'''  \n|align=center|3&ndash;2\n| {{fed|SRB}} <small>(1)</small>\n|-\n| Tennis Club Chiasso, [[Chiasso]], [[Switzerland]]\n| Outdoor clay\n| {{fed|SUI}}\n|align=center|1&ndash;3\n| '''{{fed|AUS}}''' <small>(3)</small>  \n|-\n| [[Real Club de Polo de Barcelona|Real Club de Polo]], [[Barcelona]], [[Spain]]\n| Outdoor clay\n| '''{{fed|ESP}}'''\n|align=center|4&ndash;0\n| {{fed|JPN}} <small>(4)</small>\n|-\n| [[Delray Beach Tennis Center]], [[Delray Beach]], [[United States]]\n| Outdoor hard\n| '''{{fed|USA}}''' <small>(2)</small>\n|align=center|3&ndash;2\n| {{fed|SWE}}\n|}\n\n==World Group II Play-offs==\n{{details|2013 Fed Cup World Group II Play-offs}}\nThe four losing teams from World Group II played off against qualifiers from Zonal Group I. Two teams qualified from Europe/Africa Zone, one team from the Asia/Oceania Zone, and one team from the Americas Zone.\n\nDate: 20\u201321 April\n{| class=wikitable cellspacing=\"1\" cellpadding=\"3\" style=\"border:1px solid #AAAAAA;\"\n|-\n!Venue!!Surface!!Home Team!!Score!!Visiting Team\n|-\n| Tennisclub Koksijde, [[Koksijde]], [[Belgium]]\n| Indoor hard\n| {{fed|BEL}} <small>(1)</small>\n|align=center|1\u20134\n| '''{{fed|POL}}\n|-\n| Palais des Sports de Besan\u00e7on, [[Besan\u00e7on]], [[France]] \n| Indoor hard\n| '''{{fed|FRA}}''' <small>(3)</small>\n|align=center|4\u20131\n| {{fed|KAZ}}\n|-\n| [[Estadio Mary Ter\u00e1n de Weiss]], [[Buenos Aires]], [[Argentina]]\n| Outdoor clay\n| '''{{fed|ARG}}'''\n|align=center|3\u20131\n| {{fed|GBR}} <small>(4)</small>\n|-\n| Sport Club Meridian, [[Kiev]], [[Ukraine]]\n| Indoor clay\n| {{fed|UKR}} <small>(2)</small>\n|align=center|2\u20133\n| '''{{fed|CAN}}'''\n|}\n\n== Americas Zone ==\n{{Main article|2013 Fed Cup Americas Zone}}\n* Nations in '''bold''' advanced to the higher level of competition.\n* Nations in ''italics'' were relegated down to a lower level of competition.\n\n=== Group I ===\nVenue: Country Club de Ejecutivos, [[Medell\u00edn]], [[Colombia]] (outdoor clay)\n\nDates: 6\u20139 February\n\n====Participating teams====\n{{colbegin|colwidth=18em}}\n*  {{fed|BRA}}\n*  '''{{fed|CAN}}\n*  ''{{fed|CHI}}\n*  {{fed|COL}}\n*  {{fed|MEX}}\n*  {{fed|PAR}}\n*  ''{{fed|PER}}\n*  {{fed|VEN}}\n{{colend}}\n\n=== Group II ===\nVenue: Maya Country Club, [[Santa Tecla, El Salvador|Santa Tecla]], [[El Salvador]]\n\nDates: 17\u201320 July\n\n====Participating teams====\n{{colbegin|colwidth=18em}}\n* '''{{fed|BAH}}'''\n* {{fed|BOL}}\n* {{fed|CRC}}\n* {{fed|DOM}}\n* '''{{fed|ECU}}'''\n* {{fed|ESA}}\n* {{fed|GUA}}\n* {{fed|HON}}\n* {{fed|PUR}}\n* {{fed|TRI}}\n* {{fed|URU}}\n{{colend}}\n\n== Asia/Oceania Zone ==\n{{Main article|2013 Fed Cup Asia/Oceania Zone}}\n* Nations in '''bold''' advanced to the higher level of competition.\n* Nations in ''italics'' were relegated down to a lower level of competition.\n\n=== Group I ===\nVenue: National Tennis Centre, [[Astana]], [[Kazakhstan]] (indoor hard)\n\nDates: 6\u20139 February\n\n====Participating teams====\n{{colbegin|colwidth=18em}}\n*  {{fed|CHN}}\n*  {{fed|TPE}}\n*  ''{{fed|IND}}''\n*  '''{{fed|KAZ}}'''\n*  {{fed|KOR}}\n*  {{fed|THA}}\n*  {{fed|UZB}}\n{{colend}}\n\n=== Group II ===\nVenue: National Tennis Centre, [[Astana]], [[Kazakhstan]] (indoor hard)\n\nDates: 4\u20139 February\n\n====Participating teams====\n{{colbegin|colwidth=18em}}\n* {{fed|HKG}}\n* '''{{fed|INA}}'''\n* {{fed|IRI}}\n* {{fed|KGZ}}\n* {{fed|MAS}}\n* {{fed|NZL}}\n* {{fed|PAK}}\n* {{fed|PHI}}\n* {{fed|SIN}}\n* {{fed|TKM}}\n* {{fed|VIE}}\n{{colend}}\n\n== Europe/Africa Zone ==\n{{Main article|2013 Fed Cup Europe/Africa Zone}}\n* Nations in '''bold''' advanced to the higher level of competition.\n* Nations in ''italics'' were relegated down to a lower level of competition.\n\n=== Group I ===\nVenue: Municipal Tennis Club, [[Eilat]], [[Israel]] (outdoor hard)\n\nDates: 6\u201310 February\n\n====Participating teams====\n{{colbegin|colwidth=18em}}\n* {{fed|AUT}}\n* {{fed|BLR}}\n* ''{{fed|BIH}}''\n* {{fed|BUL}}\n* {{fed|CRO}}\n* ''{{fed|GEO}}''\n* '''{{fed|GBR}}'''\n* {{fed|HUN}}\n* {{fed|ISR}}\n* {{fed|LUX}}\n* {{fed|NED}}\n* '''{{fed|POL}}'''\n* {{fed|POR}}\n* {{fed|ROM}}\n* {{fed|SLO}}\n* {{fed|TUR}}\n{{colend}}\n\n===Pools===\n{{col-float-begin|width=35em}}\n{{4TeamRR\n|title='''[[2013 Fed Cup Europe/Africa Zone Group I \u2013 Pool A|Pool A]]\n|team-1-abbrev=CRO\n|team-1={{nowrap|{{fed|CRO}}}} (3\u20130)\n|team-2-abbrev=BLR\n|team-2={{fed|BLR}} (2\u20131)\n|team-3-abbrev=AUT\n|team-3={{fed|AUT}} (1\u20132)\n|team-4-abbrev=GEO\n|team-4={{nowrap|{{fed|GEO}}}} (0\u20133)\n|1v2=3\u20130|1v3=2\u20131|1v4=3\u20130\n|2v1=0\u20133|2v3=2\u20131|2v4=3\u20130\n|3v1=1\u20132|3v2=1\u20132|3v4=3\u20130\n|4v1=0\u20133|4v2=0\u20133|4v3=0\u20133\n}}\n{{col-float-break|width=35em}}\n{{4TeamRR\n|title='''[[2013 Fed Cup Europe/Africa Zone Group I \u2013 Pool B|Pool B]]\n|team-1-abbrev=GBR\n|team-1={{fed|GBR}} (3\u20130)\n|team-2-abbrev=HUN\n|team-2={{fed|HUN}} (2\u20131)\n|team-3-abbrev=POR\n|team-3={{fed|POR}} (1\u20132)\n|team-4-abbrev=BIH\n|team-4={{nowrap|{{fed|BIH}} (0\u20133)}}\n|1v2=2\u20131|1v3=2\u20131|1v4=3\u20130\n|2v1=1\u20132|2v3=3\u20130|2v4